review_blob: Bottle: Opaque orange on color with some hazyness.  Smells of grapefruit and other citrus on first wif.  Very much citrus flavor with nice balanced hoppy finish.  Overall a very good IPA.
Bottle:  Smellls like cut grass mixed with corn.  Clear golden in color with normal white head.  Slight hop in taste with finishes of corn.  Nice have a few beer.
Bottle:  Copper in color with almost opaque head.  Extremely malty smell with hints of caramel.  Taset is same as aroma with an alcoholish finish.  Nice overall.
Bottle: Pale yellow in color with smoky white head.  Somewhat piney in aroma with hints of sweetness, possibly caramel.   Fruity initail on palate with long lasting bitter finish.
beer_name: Big Sky Scape Goat Pale Ale

review_blob: Bottle: I bought this bottle strait from the Brewery in New Glarus.  Medium brown in color with very pale brown head.  A little thicker than other dark ales.  definate smell of nuts,almond maybe hazelnut.  Same in the taste with a nice hopy finish.
beer_name: New Glarus Fat Squirrel Nut Brown Ale

review_blob: Bottle: I bought this bottle strait from the Brewery in New Glarus.  Very pale in color with white cloud-like head.  Very basic.  Slightly corny in aroma, with the same in flavor.  Hints of some light hop on the finish.  Great refreshing beer on a hot summer day.
beer_name: New Glarus Totally Naked Extra Pale Lager

review_blob: Sampled in frosty mug 1 block away from the brewery at The Village Green Bar.  Initial smell of wheat and corn with hints of lemon.  Sudsy head with no lacing.  very pale and cloudy almost orange in color.  Fizzy and smooth on palate.  Nice wheat beer with slight hop finish.  Refreshing on a hot day!

Sampled on tap 1 block away from the brewery at The Village Green Bar.  Initial aroma of berries and spice with sweet malts accents.  Light amber in color with lots of carbonation.  Medium lacing with soapy white head.  Light carbonation on the palate.  Very spicy sweet flavors with medium hop finish.

On tap at brew pub:  Poured mahogany red with a fuzzy beige head.  Aroma is of peat smoke.  Lots of malt sweetness, cherries and dark fruits.  Good lacing along edge of glass.  Plate is medium and crisp.

On tap at brew pub:  Poured deep mahogany brown with small beige head.  Big caramel aroma with hints of black licorice.  flavors of black licorice char with a lot of caramel sweetness.  Palate is a little light with lots of carbonation which creates a dryness.
On tap at brew pub:  Pours cloudy caramel red with small off white head.  Aroma thick earthy malty. Big body. Rich and velvety.  Alcohol is present but covered up by sweetness.
Bottle: Dark motor oil in color with slight butterscotch head.  Some light lacing at first but diminishing quickly.  Smoky char flavor with hints of chocloate.  A very nice tingle on the palate.
Poured gloden brown with thick soapy white head.  Some hints of citrus or maybe floral hops. Very smooth with just a little dry hoppy finish
Initial smell of chocolate and some smoked coffee malts.  Opaque brown in color with khaki colored head with sparse lacing.  Smoked hop initial flavor with an amazing burnt char finish.
Red caramel somewhat hazy in color. Small head with no lacing.  Very slight caramel hop with light body.  Great summer time beer!  Fat Tire??
beer_name: Harbor City Mile Rock Amber Ale

review_blob: Initial appearance honey orange. Very clear virtually no head.  No lacing.  Extreme citrus hops on first wif with taste the same.  Definite grapefruit hints throughout. Thanks to TannerTavernboys for the sample.

2006 Vintage: This beer has so much going on. Very Complex. Pitch black in color with red orange rim in glass.  Slight lacing with heavy legs once brought to room temperature.  Flavor is amazing cant really explain: Caramel, coffee, char, dark chocolate, black licorice.  This is defiantly a top 50 beer for a reason.  YOU HAVE TO TRY THIS ONE!!!!  Thanks to TannerTavern boys for the sample.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: On tap at brewery:  Golden yellow with light tan head.  Slightly bitter.  Some malt and spice in aroma.  Light bodied.  Slightly sweet, maybe grape.  Kind of basic.
On tap at brewery:  Initial smell of butterscotch and chestnuts.  Dark golden brown in color with a soapy off white head.  Smooth on palate.  Very nutty and butterscotch flavor just like smell.
On tap at brewery:  Slight pine hop in smell.  Some caramel.  Very pale orange/red color.  Sweet initial flavor with minimal flavor in middle.  Slight citrus hop finish.
On Tap at brewery: Sweet char malt\evergreen on smell.  Dark mahogany appearance.  Sweet, very smooth on palate.  Nice carbonation.  Very dry finish with some hops.

tap at brewpub-pours cloudy oragne unfiltered with lots of hop and/or yeast particulates. aroma is big grapefruit-can definately be used as an aid to clear the sinuses for shure! so much grapefruit that it starts to smell like cleaning solution. lots of pine/grapefruit on the flavors with very little notes of any malt. hops go from pine to citric on the finish with lingering orange and lemon notes. not very complex but aids as a good hop machine.  I drank this with Tanner Tavernboys and we collectively rated this one.

tap at brewpub-pours hazy amber/carmel with great lacing from start to finish. Big oak/burbon notes with the undertone of buttery vanilla. Vanilla, currants, dark cherries, some alcohol blend together very well. alcohol is somewhat present, but adds sweetness and rounds everything out. Palate is lush, thick and quite sweet. Palate verges on cloying. Well done and definately worth a try!  I drank this with TannerTavernboys and we rated together.
beer_name: Carlyle Bourbon Barrel American Strong Ale

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Tap: Light redish brown in color with little head.  Definate taste of hops, however some hints of raspberry.  WIERD!  Some other fruit was present.
Bottle:  Poured dark brown with thick medium lasting head.  Definate chocolate coffee type roasted malts with just enough hop to make it a great beer.

On tap at the brewpub:  Came out hazy with quickly diminishing head.  Definate fruity and lots of citrus taste on first sip. Almost soapy flavor probably thr grassy hops.  Not bad overall but by far not  their best.

On tap (nitrous) at the brewpub:  Very unclear light golden in color.  Nice thick long lasting head with strong lacing.  Not much on the nose however definate taste of hops.  Some fruity possibale floral hints in the flavor.

Tap at the brewpub:  Light color for a stout but still really dark in color.  Definate smell of cherry and possible roasted malts.  As far as taste:  Excellent!  Some flavor of barrel however mostly choclate and cherry.  Kind of mild overall but definatly not a bad thing.  One of the better cherry stouts out there.

Tap at the brewpub:  Very light in color with minimal haed.  Definate vanilla on initial smell with a little spice on second sniff.  Great vanilla taste with no real difference in the finish.  A great sweet lighter beer!
Bottle: Light in color with little to no head.  Nice corn flavor with little taste of anything else. Nice refreshing summer beer.  Better than Corona.
Bottle:  Strong hints of corn on initial smell.  Taste is the same corn.  Have to gove some credit because it is an original flavor.  Havent had anything else like it.

Bottle:  Batch #7182:  Poured very dark brown that verry little light can be seen through.  Long lasting medium brown head.  Has great dark chocolate, sweet maltand some coffee tones in the smell.  Taste is as it smells  PERFECT!
Bottle:At first smell definate hops, but second smell has a hint of sweetness.  Roasted malt and chocolate.  Nice sweet short lasting finish.

Bottle:Pours almost black wittle light shining through.  Long lasting light brown thick head.  
Strong tastes of chocolate and dark roasted coffee.  Well Done!

Bottle:At first wif their is an undistinguishable sweet very fruity smell.  Light almost opaque red in color with very little head.  Hints of cranberry at first sip and goes nowwhere fast.  Very dry bitter like a lemon finish.  WIERD BEER!!!
Bottle:Poured cloudy with little head.  nice citris hop initial flavor.  Finish a little malty.  Not to bad.
Bottle:loght brown with an orange cast.  light on the carbination side though.  Sweet fruity aroma with distinct pine hop taste.  finish is the same as the taste, piney!
Bottle:  Light golden brown with quick diminishing head.  A little hoppy at first taste going quickly to nothing.
Bottle: Not much to talk about as far as aroma.  Decent head with little carbonation.  This is the Miller Light of Japan.  Really bland and watery
Bottle:Initial smell of fruit maybe apple.  poured cloudy light brown with long lasting golden head.  Definate bananna flavor all the way through.
Bottle:Initial smell of fruity possibly honey malts. As far as taste: EXCELLENT!  Initial honey with a hint of citrus.  Finish just a bit bitter.  The sweet aftertaste stays with you for a while.
beer_name: Krasniy Vostok Bogemskoe (Bogemia Pale Beer / Bogemian)

review_blob: Bottle: Golden color with a slim white head. Aroma of corn and malts with a hint of fruit.  Taste is somewhat hopish with a weird chemical aftertaste.
Bottle:Poured light brown with thick quickly diminishing head. Smell was of corn and really light hop.  Very corny and ricy.  i dont know what they drink in Greece, but if this is it I wont go there.

Bottle:  Poured golden brown with short lasting off white head.  Slight hopy smell with hints of citrus.  Initial flavor of strong hops with again, a grassy citrus finish.  One of the best Polish beers I have tasted so far.

BOTTLE:Nice dark golden color with smoothe off white head.  Slightly bitter smell, however I have a cold and I cantt smell well.   Somewhat sweet with a real bitter hop finish.  There is a hint of something else but cant put a finger on it.  This seems like an every day drinker over in Poland, however a pretty good beer.

BOTTLE: Poured nice with thick white head.   Light caramel color with hints of berry on the smell.  Smooth sweet taste with slight hops on the finish.  Not as bad as the ratings.  A refreshing sweet pale beer.

Actually a Crystal Lager.  I got the redirect when i found Crystal.   Nice golden brown color with slightly fruity and bitter aroma.  Definate light hop taste with an almost carmel malt finish.  Nice balence between the two.
Light brown in color and opaque.  Head is almost blonde.  Has some lacing, however aroma is slightly hoppy.  Polish Irish Beer?
Poured light pink with pale white head.  Almost looke like ice tea.  Definate raspberry  smell with some hops.  Very sweet beer and kind of watered down.  This reminds me ofKLipton Rasberrty Tea.
Can:Great beer pours real light.  Light brown head with hints of roasted malts.  Has juat a little taste of hops.
